Introduction

Jinsol is an independent South Korean singer-songwriter. She is a former member of the girl group APRIL.

Jinsol has trained for 6 months in 2015 at DSP Media before making her first debut as a member of APRIL on August 24.

On January 30, 2019, DSP Media announced the release of a new single album, which would be sung by a special sub-unit made up of Jinsol and Naeun. On February 7, the single, titled " My Story ", was released.

On January 28, 2022, DSP Media announced that April has decided to disband after 6 years and go their separate ways. On July 28, 2022, she signed an exclusive contract with STORY&PLUS. On September 18, 2023, it was reported that she had signed an exclusive contract with 220 Entertainment.
